Work Summary:
Session was conducted on CSS Layouts, Flexbox, and Responsive Design Basics 
Traditional layout techniques such as block and inline elements were briefly reviewed, followed by modern layout systems.
A major focus of the session was on Flexbox (Flexible Box Layout). We learned how Flexbox helps in aligning and distributing space among elements efficiently. 
Important properties such as display: flex, flex-direction, justify-content, align-items, flex-wrap, and gap were explained with practical examples. 
The session then covered Responsive Design Basics, emphasizing the importance of designing websites that work seamlessly across desktops, tablets, and mobile devices.
We were introduced to concepts like fluid layouts, percentage-based widths, viewport units, and media queries. 
The use of @media rules to apply different styles for different screen sizes was demonstrated.



Learning Outcomes :

Understood modern CSS layout techniques
Learned how to use Flexbox for alignment and spacing
Gained knowledge of responsive design principles
Learned how to apply media queries for different screen sizes
Successfully built a simple responsive webpage using Flexbox
